15 constituting parts of a common scheme or course of conduct is a severity
16 level 9, nonperson felony; and
17 (9) property that is livestock or an implement of husbandry is a
18 severity level 5, nonperson felony.
19 (c) As used in this section:
20 (1) "Conviction" or "convicted" includes being convicted of a
21 violation of K.S.A. 21-3701, prior to its repeal, this section or a municipal
22 ordinance which prohibits the acts that this section prohibits;
23 (2) "implement of husbandry" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 8-
24 126, and amendments thereto;
25 (3) "livestock" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 22-4807a, and
26 amendments thereto;
27 (4) "mail" means a letter, postal card, package or bag sent through the
28 United States postal service or other delivery service, or any other article
29 or thing contained therein;
30 (3)(5) "regulated scrap metal" means the same as defined in K.S.A.
31 2024 Supp. 50-6,109, and amendments thereto;
32 (4)(6) "remote service unit" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 9-
33 1111, and amendments thereto, and includes, but is not limited to,
34 automated cash dispensing machines and automated teller machines; and
35 (5)(7) "value" means the value of the property or, if the property is
36 regulated scrap metal or a remote service unit, the cost to restore the site of
37 the theft of such regulated scrap metal or remote service unit to its
38 condition at the time immediately prior to the theft of such regulated scrap
39 metal or remote service unit, whichever is greater.
40 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 22-4807a is hereby amended to read as follows: 22-
41 4807a. (a) The following property is subject to forfeiture pursuant to this
42 act:
43 (1) Contraband property used or intended to be used in the

