1 commission of theft of livestock or an implement of husbandry;
2 (2) the proceeds gained from the commission of theft of livestock or
3 an implement of husbandry;
4 (3) personal property acquired with proceeds gained from the
5 commission of theft of livestock or an implement of husbandry;
6 (4) all conveyances, including aircraft, vehicles, vessels, horses or
7 dogs which that are used or intended for the use to transport or in any
8 manner to facilitate the transportation for the purpose of the commission of
9 theft of livestock or an implement of husbandry. No conveyance used by
10 any person as a common carrier in the transportation of business as a
11 common carrier is subject to forfeiture under this section unless it appears
12 that the owner or other person in charge of the conveyance is a consenting
13 party or privy to a violation of this act. No conveyance is subject to
14 forfeiture under this section by reason of any act or omission established
15 by the owners thereof to have been committed or omitted without the
16 owners knowledge or consent. A forfeiture of a conveyance encumbered
17 by a bona fide security interest is subject to the interest of the secured
18 party or parties;
19 (5) all books, records and research products and materials including
20 microfilm, tapes and data which, whether in a physical or electronic
21 format, that are used or intended for the use in the theft of livestock or an
22 implement of husbandry;
23 (6) everything of value furnished, or intended to be furnished, or
24 traded or used as payment or invested for anything of value but shall not
25 include real property. It may be presumed that this property was acquired
26 with proceeds gained from the commission of theft of livestock or an
27 implement of husbandry and are subject to forfeiture.
28 (b) Property which that is used in the commission of theft of
29 livestock which or an implement of husbandry that has title of ownership
30 with two parties on the title or a cosigner is subject to forfeiture, if one
31 party on the title uses the property in the commission of theft of livestock
32 or an implement of husbandry or receives titled property as the proceeds of
33 such felony even if the second party claims that such second party did not
34 have knowledge or involvement in such felony.
35 (c) As used in this act:
36 (1) "Contraband property" means property of any nature including
37 personal, tangible or intangible but shall does not include real property.
38 (2) "Domesticated deer" means any member of the family cervidae
39 that was legally obtained and is being sold or raised in a confined area
40 for:
41 (A) Breeding stock;
42 (B) any carcass, skin or part of such animal;
43 (C) exhibition; or

